author: Financial News
title: Deutsche Bank markets e-trading chief to leave
text:
Follow @_TimCave 23 October 2015 Deutsche Bank's head of markets electronic trading is leaving at the start of November, marking the latest departure from the German bank's trading business, which is braced for fresh change amid an overhaul creating separate sales and trading and investment banking divisions.
